Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/swap-salary/

Problem: Write an SQL query to swap all 'f' and 'm' values (i.e., change all 'f' values to 'm' and vice versa) with a single update statement and no intermediate temporary tables.
Note that you must write a single update statement, do not write any select statement for this problem.

Code:
UPDATE salary
    SET sex = if(sex= 'm', 'f','m');
    
    
    
Output: 
| id | name | sex | salary |
| -- | ---- | --- | ------ |
| 1  | A    | f   | 2500   |
| 2  | B    | m   | 1500   |
| 3  | C    | f   | 5500   |
